    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The bug is in `PopupMenu.qml` implementation:\r\n```\r\n            Image {\r\n                id: menuIcon\r\n                source: popupMenuItem.icon.source\r\n                visible: false\r\n                width: parent.width\r\n                height: parent.width\r\n                sourceSize.width: width\r\n                sourceSize.height: height\r\n            }\r\n```\r\nit is incorrect to set `sourceSize` to the final rendering Image size. The `sourceSize` property must always match the original SVG size. Then width and height properties of Image can specify the desired rendering canvas size. What makes this even worse - most SVG icons we use in Menus have different sizes.\r\n\r\nHow to fix:\r\nEvery `Action` that has `icon` property set, must always specify `width` and `height` of the original SVG (need to manually open each SVG and check the size). These values we will assign to `sourceSize: Qt.size(popupMenuIcon.icon.width, popupMenuIcon.icon.height)`. Next, since all icons in a given menu must have the same final rendering size (e.g. 16x16), we should introduce a property on PopupMenu item that defines the common icons size, e.g. `iconsSize`. Then `indicator: Item {` must be always sized to `popupMenu.iconsSize` and then `menuIcon` should be aligned inside the parent item using proper scaling/fit mode. ",
